		<div class="faq">
			<div class="faq-header">
				FAQs
			</div>
			<div class="pure-g faq-body">
				<div class="pure-u-1-3 faq-col">
					<b>What kind of bike is right for me?</b>
					<p>
					Stop by our store and ask any of our employees and they’ll run down everything you need to know to find the perfect bike for you!</p>
					<!-- <br> -->
					<b>How can I tell what size bike I need?</b>
					<p>
					The best way would be to visit our store to try one out for yourself. One of our employees can give an accurate size recommendation for you to test out.</p>
					<b>My bike is functioning weirdly, what should I do?</b>
					<p>
					If your bike is one you bought from Cycle Fitness, the first step is to take your bicycle to our store and we will have one of our repair-certified employees check it out and give you a rundown of what you can do to fix it.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="pure-u-1-3 faq-col">
					<b>Do you offer a warranty on your bikes?</b>
					<p>
					All of our products come with a 90-day warranty for cost-free replacement of dysfunctional parts.</p>
					<!-- <br> -->
					<b>What is your return policy?</b>
					<p>
					We offer a 30-day return policy if you are unsatisfied with your purchase. All you need is a receipt to receive a full refund.</p>
          <!-- <br> -->
					<b>What equipment do I need to ride a bike?</b>
					<p>
					The most important equipment you need are a helmet and safety lights or reflectors. If you are riding in a city or in the dark, a reflective vest may also be a good investment.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="pure-u-1-3 faq-col">
					<b>Where are your seminars held?</b>
					<p>
					The seminars are held on-site weekly at our store in 123 Avenue of the America, New York, NY 20013.</p>
					<!-- <br> -->
					<b>Where are your cycling trips held?</b>
					<p>
					The location of our cycling trips varies each month - check out our events page to see where the next one will be held! </p>
          <b>Is your whole catalog available online?</b>
          <p>
          Most of what is on our catalog is available in-store and in-stock, but it may take us some time to keep our catalog up-to-date.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

